Dear Southwest Louisiana Charter Academy Family,

We continue to pray for all of you. Like so many of your homes, our schools have suffered significant damage. As a result of the damage, we will not be reopening in the near future. Aside from the clean-up and repairs that are necessary, our immediate concern is for the safety of our students and staff. When we are better able to determine our timeline, we will provide that to you. Please continue to check here and our website for updates and resources.
We wish you all continued safety.

post_text:
Dear Bulldog Nation,

In light of the racial injustices going on today, we strive for peace and equity within our schools. We hope and pray that we can encourage our students to love each other, because we know together we can make a difference. We will continue our passionate pursuit of excellent education for all children and use that as a means to change the dynamics of a broken system. There is no place for racism, hatred, or social injustice in our school and in our world. We ask that you join us in the commitment to keeping these promises to our students and families.

With kind regards,

Kim Lewis, Principal
CSUSA - Louisiana

post_text:
Dear Parents,

As per Gov. John Bel Edwards all Louisiana K-12 schools will be closed starting on Monday. Here are a few updates as it relates to SWLCA:

1. School will be closed from March 16 - April 13.
2. There will be no Saturday school.
3. There will be no after school activities on today.
4. At-Home lesson packets will be sent with all students.
5. We will contact all parents with our plan to incorporate online instruction.

We will keep all parents informed as we obtain more information.

Please be safe and God bless!
Principal Lewis

Girlie Girls Founder, Anita Barker joins Southwest for Read Across America Day by reading to Mrs. Glaude’s kindergarten class.

Girlie Girls is a non-profit organization dedicated to nurturing and empowering young ladies ages 12-18 years of age to achieve their full potentials in becoming influential and active members of their communities and society. This is accomplished through year-round mentoring, promoting academic excellence with support, building social awareness and positive relationships, elevating self-esteem and self-confidence, providing leadership and community service opportunities, learning life skills through trainings, seminars, and conferences, connecting with positive role models, taking fieldtrips, attending Girlie Girls gatherings, and so much more.

Thanks Anita Barker for sharing a piece of you with our students.

post_text:
Ms. Cheramie’s STEM and 2nd classes made snow. Her STEM classes learned how baking soda (sodium bicarbonate) mixed with shaving cream (acid compound) creates a mixture that is cold to the touch, which is known as an endothermic reaction.

Her 2nd graders also learned about it after reading “The Story of Snow.” Her STEM classes also graphed coordinates to make a decorated Christmas tree.

post_text:
7th grade science students at SWLCA completed their Thermal Energy unit by designing and constructing solar cookers and coolers, while utilizing their knowledge of conductors and insulators.

The solar cookers were created to test if it could melt a s'more and the coolers were created to test whether it could keep a freeze pop from melting.

#SWLCAEngineers
#WeDoScience
text:
7th grade science students at SWLCA completed their Thermal Energy unit by designing and constructing solar cookers and coolers, while utilizing their knowledge of conductors and insulators.

The solar cookers were created to test if it could melt a s'more and the coolers were created to test whether it could keep a freeze pop from melting.

#SWLCAEngineers

post_text:
Here at Southwest Louisiana Charter Academy, we don't just teach our students how to be great test-takers... We teach them how to be great human beings!!! Human beings who care about one another. Human beings who encourage one another and show love for one another.

Meet Keith and Logan... 2 friends from 2 different backgrounds who share the same Bulldog Pride.

Today, Keith surprised Logan with a pair of tennis shoes. When asked why did he do this he stated, "I wanted to do this for Logan just because he's my friend and a good guy!" Logan responded back in excitement, "Yes. He is my friend!!!"

Huge Shout-Outs to Keith and Logan for displaying what true Bulldog Pride and friendship looks like!!!
